3.18.24  7:03 pm   PLEASE tell me that a song without lyrics is still considered music/a song. i'm going crazy about this and i'd like to make sure i'm not crazy.

     sure it is

     i recommended a song to my friend the other day and he complained about the lack of lyrics (there were some, but it was mostly sounds). and he was like "what's the point if it doesn't have lyrics?" and it just irked me badly! because i think some of the most beautiful, moving stuff you hear won't have lyrics at all. that's still considered music, no? i mean, who is anyone to put constraints on music like that whatever

     it can be tough to latch onto something without words or images. it's ok that you can do it, it's ok that he can't do it. no need for irkation. he's not putting any constraints on music any more than colorblind people are putting restraints on their own color vision
